===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ja|en}} {{m|ja|sc=Jpan|武士道|tr=</i>ぶしどう<i>, bushidō}}, from {{etyl|ltc|en}} [[武士]] (''mjú-dʐí'' "warrior") (compare {{etyl|cmn|-}} ''wǔshì'' 武士, Cantonese ''mou<sup>5</sup>-si<sup>6</sup>'' 武士) + 道 (''dáu'' "way").

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# An [[ethical]] [[code]] of the [[samurai]] that was prevalent in [[feudal]] [[Japan]] that advocated unquestioning [[loyalty]] to the [[master]] at all costs and [[obedience]] in all deeds, valuing [[honor]] above [[life]].

